data.chText: （在品质上）更好的；占优势；更胜一筹
data.enText: better in quality than sb/sth else; greater than sb/sth else
vastly superior
superior intelligence

data.chText: 这一款式在技术上超过了与之竞争的产品。
data.enText: This model is technically superior to its competitors.

data.chText: 利物浦队明显更胜一筹。
data.enText: Liverpool were clearly the superior team.

data.chText: 敌人由于在人数上占优而取胜。
data.enText: The enemy won because of their superior numbers (= there were more of them) .

data.chText: （在级别、重要性或职位上）更高的
data.enText: higher in rank, importance or position
my superior officer
superior status
a superior court of law
showing by your behaviour that you think you are better than others
a superior manner

data.chText: 他总是显得那么有优越感。
data.enText: He always looks so superior.

data.chText: 质量卓越的；出类拔萃的；超群的
data.enText: of very good quality; better than other similar things
superior apartments

data.chText: 级别（或地位、职位）更高的人；上级；上司
data.enText: a person of higher rank, status or position

data.chText: 社会地位比自己高的人
data.enText: your social superiors
He's my immediate superior (= the person directly above me) .

data.chText: 我要去找你的上级投诉。
data.enText: I'm going to complain to your superiors.
used in titles for the head of a religious community
Mother Superior

word_means: 用作宗教团体领导的头衔
simple_means.memory_skill: super 上 + ior 较…的 → 较高的

means: (在级别、重要性或职位上)更高的
级别(或地位、职位)更高的人
用作宗教团体领导的头衔

tr: a character or symbol set or printed or written above and immediately to one side of another character
the head of a religious community
one of greater rank or station or quality
a combatant who is able to defeat rivals
(sometimes followed by `to') not subject to or influenced by
example: trust magnates who felt themselves superior to law

tr: of or characteristic of high rank or importance
of high or superior quality or performance
having an orbit farther from the sun than the Earth's orbit
example: Mars and Jupiter are the closest in of the superior planets

tr: written or printed above and to one side of another character

value.def: If one thing or person is superior to another, the first is better than the second.

example.ex: We have a relationship infinitely superior to those of many of our friends...
example.tran: 我们的关系要比我们其他许多朋友的关系好得多。

example.ex: ...a woman greatly superior to her husband in education and sensitivity...
example.tran: 学历和悟性都比她丈夫高出许多的女人

example.ex: Long-term stock market investments have produced superior returns compared with cash deposits.
example.tran: 股票市场长期投资的收益比现金存款要高。

example.ex: The technical superiority of laser discs over tape is well established.
example.tran: 激光影碟相对于磁带的技术优势早已牢牢确立。

value.def: If you describe something as superior, you mean that it is good, and better than other things of the same kind.

example.ex: A few years ago it was virtually impossible to find superior quality coffee in local shops...
example.tran: 几年前在当地商店里几乎买不到优质咖啡。

example.ex: Lulu was said to be of very superior intelligence.
example.tran: 大家都说露露智力出众。

value.def: A superior person or thing is more important than another person or thing in the same organization or system.

example.ex: ...negotiations between the mutineers and their superior officers...
example.tran: 哗变士兵和他们的上司长官间的谈判

example.ex: Locally passed laws are of superior authority to those laws passed in Moscow.
example.tran: 当地法律高于莫斯科颁布的全国法律。

value.tran: (在重要性上)更高级的，上级的

value.def: Your superior in an organization that you work for is a person who has a higher rank than you.

example.ex: Other army units are completely surrounded and cut-off from communication with their superiors...
example.tran: 其他陆军部队被重重包围，和上级的联系也被切断了。

example.ex: The company president, and my immediate superior, was the dynamic Harry Stokes.
example.tran: 公司的董事长，也就是我的直接上司，是精力充沛的哈里·斯托克斯。

value.tran: 上级;上司;级别更高的人

value.def: If you describe someone as superior, you disapprove of them because they behave as if they are better, more important, or more intelligent than other people.

example.ex: You can stand there and feel superior as you point and laugh at them.
example.tran: 你站在那儿指指点点、嘲笑他们时，会觉得自己高人一等。

value.tran: 有优越感的;高傲的;傲慢的

example.ex: ...a false sense of his superiority over mere journalists.
example.tran: 他在微不足道的记者面前所表现出的一种虚妄的优越感

value.def: If one group of people has superior numbers to another group, the first has more people than the second, and therefore has an advantage over it.

example.ex: The demonstrators fled when they saw the authorities' superior numbers...
example.tran: 看到当局派出人员人数占优，示威者就四散逃跑了。

example.ex: His men were far superior numerically.
example.tran: 他手下的士兵在人数上占了绝对优势。

value.def: If you describe someone as your superior in a particular activity, you mean that they are better than you at that activity.

example.ex: Anthony sometimes felt that his mistress was his superior in willpower...
example.tran: 有时安东尼感觉他的情妇比他更有意志力。

example.ex: Among his immediate rivals was Arnold Matters, probably his superior in comic roles.
example.tran: 在他的直接竞争者中，阿诺德·马特斯也许在喜剧表演上比他更胜一筹。
